alician: Castilianized form of   Pontes  ."]}]},{"name":"Marie","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Maria .  When first introduced to England in the Middle Ages, it was Anglicized in pronunciation and respelled   Mary .  This French form was reintroduced into the English-speaking world as a separate name in the 19th century, and is still pronounced more or less in the French manner, although sometimes with the stress on the first syllable. It is now often used in combination with other names such as <i>Ellie</i>, <i>Chloe</i>, and <i>Lisa</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Marie de Pottes was born in 1325, in France, her father, Gérard V de la Pottes, seigneur de Pottes et Pétriaux, was 30 and her mother, Yolande de Lalaing, was 25. She married Jean I de Haynin in 1340, in France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1382, in Valenciennes, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, at the age of 57."},"et":{"1325–1382":"1325–1382","1325–1365":"1325–1365","1310–1340":"1310–1340","1340–1402":"1340–1402","1348–1428":"1348–1428","1349–1410":"1349–1410","1295–1342":"1295–1342","1300–1326":"1300–1326","1340":"1340","1295":"1295","1382":"1382","1349":"1349","1326":"1326","1348":"1348","1325":"1325","1402":"1402","1300":"1300","1410":"1410","1365":"1365","1310":"1310","1342":"1342","1428":"1428","Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Valenciennes,France":"Valenciennes, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1325–1382":"1325–1382","1325–1365":"1325–1365","1310–1340":"1310–1340","1340–1402":"1340–1402","1348–1428":"1348–1428","1349–1410":"1349–1410","1295–1342":"1295–1342","1300–1326":"1300–1326","1340":"1340","1295":"1295","1382":"1382","1349":"1349","1326":"1326","1348":"1348","1325":"1325","1402":"1402","1300":"1300","1410":"1410","1365":"1365","1310":"1310","1342":